        <p id= "the-steps"><strong>Step 1:</strong> preheat oven to 4:00. line baking sheet with parchment paper.
</p> 
<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> add water, brown sugar, salt, vannilla, and 4 TBsp butter to pot, set over medium heat, stir until butter is melted. </p>

      <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> add flour, stir with rubber spatula until a thick paste forms.</p> 
      
       <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> cook dough for 1 minute, mixing constantly, until a smooth ball of dough forms, tern off heat and set aside.</p>
     
      <p><strong>Step 5:</strong> crack egg in large bowl, throw away shell and wash your hands, whisk until smooth.</p>
      
       <p><strong>Step 6:</strong> add dough to egg, mix vigorously with large whisk until fully   incorporated.</p>
      
     
       <p><strong>Step 7:</strong> prepare pastry bag </p> 
      
      <p><strong>Step 8:</strong>
      squeeze batter to make a 3-inch log, use a knife to cut to size.</p> 
      
       <p><strong>Step 9:</strong> 
        melt 1 TBsp butter in microwave-safe bowl for 30 seconds, use a pastry brush to paint butter on churros.</p> 
     <p><strong>Step 10:</strong> bake 25-27 minutes, until churrows are crisp and ridges are thoroughly browned.</p> 
      <p><strong>Step 11:</strong> combine sugar and cinnamon in large resealable bag, add 6 warm churros, shake to coat, repeat to finish</p> 
     
    
    
    
   <p id="strong-fill"><strong>see how to fill a pastry bag</strong></p>
   <p id= "fill-pastry"> secure the piping tip on the outside of the pastry bag, using a coupler ring<br>1 insert the coupler base into the pastry bag,
   if necessary snip off the tip of the pastry bag to expose the tip of the coupler base,<br>
   2 drop the piping tip into the coupler ring,<br>
   3 screw the coupler ring onto the coupler base with the thin pastry bag between.</P>
   
   
   <p> <strong>filling the pastry bag<br></strong>
    place the prepard pastry bag into a tall drinking glass fold the top of the bag with batter or frosting. 
    </p><p><strong>using the pastry bag<br></strong>
     once filled gather the top of the bag together and gently twist, use your writing hand to hold the bag closed and gently apply pressure, use your other hand as a guide for the piping tip.</p>
